data.title: New Wet Kojak
data.meta_description:
New Wet Kojak.
Washington, D.C..
New Wet Kojak was formed in 1993 by guitarist/singer Scott McCloud + bassist Johnny Temple – both of Girls Against Boys + Soulside. They created an overtly seductive aesthetic on their albums – utilizing the saxophone, whispered vocals and reserved instrumentation. 
The band also includes Geoff Turner on lead guitar/keyboard + and Charles Bennington on saxophone and Nick Pelliciotto on drums.
